gomodel:SYNGO_2805  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"CRD-FZD9 blocks the calcium increase produced by Wnt-5a\"\n- \"Because Wnt-5a triggers an increase in intracellular Ca2+ concentration in hippocampal neurons (13), we attempted to understand the potential role of FZD9 in this effect by measuring the intracellular Ca2+ changes using the molecular probe Fura-2 AM. As expected, Wnt-5a treatment induced a rapid increase in the intensity of the Fura-2 AM signal (340/380 ratio), indicating a positive signaling modulation in intracellular Ca2+. Treatment with CRD-FZD9 blocked the Wnt-5a-mediated increase in the Ca2+ concentrations, whereas CRD-FZD9 has no effect (Fig. 2B). \"\n\nFig.4: \"FZD9 down-expression impairs Wnt-5a signaling\"\n- \"These experiments reveal that down-regulation of endogenous FZD9 selectively impairs the Wnt-5a-induced rapid increase in intracellular Ca2+ concentrations in hippocampal neurons.\"\n- \"As shown in Fig. 4E, Wnt-5a treatment induced an increase in the number of dendritic protrusions in Fux-EGFP-transfected neurons, with a maximal effect at 2 h; however, this effect was reduced to basal levels in shFZD9-transfected neurons. \". Experimental description: - \"Rat hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day ...\"\n- Species of Wnt5a is human and mouse (identical aa sequences; traced back via supplier R&D systems)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2805" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

